 Service</strong><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0845 601 2001 (option 2)<br />\n<strong>Textphone:</strong> 0845 601 2002</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Questions you can&rsquo;t ask when recruiting</h2>\n\n<p>You must not ask candidates about <a href=\"/discrimination-your-rights/types-of-discrimination\" title=\"Types of discrimination\">protected characteristics</a> and:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>their health</li>\n  <li>if they&rsquo;re married, single or in a civil partnership</li>\n  <li>if they have children or plan to have children </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You <strong>can</strong> ask about about health or <a href=\"/recruitment-disabled-people\" title=\"Recruitment and disabled people\">disability</a> if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>there are necessary requirements of the job that can&rsquo;t be met with <a href=\"/reasonable-adjustments-for-disabled-workers\" title=\"Reasonable adjustments for disabled workers\">reasonable adjustments</a></li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re finding out if someone needs help to take part in a selection test or interview</li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re using &lsquo;<a href=\"/recruitment-disabled-people/encouraging-applications\" title=\"Encouraging applications\">positive action</a>&rsquo; to recruit a disabled person</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Even if you use a recruitment agency you might be liable if any discrimination happens during their recruitment process.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Date of birth</h2>\n<p>You can&rsquo;t ask someone for their date of birth on an application form. You can only include this as part of an equality monitoring form if you use one. </p>\n\n<h2>Criminal convictions</h2>\n\n<p>Applicants don&rsquo;t have to tell you about <a href=\"/employers-checks-job-applicants\" title=\"Checks employers can make on job applicants\">criminal convictions</a> if they&rsquo;re spent. You must treat the applicant as if the conviction has not happened, and cannot refuse to employ the person because of their conviction.</p>\n\n<p>There are some areas of employment that are exempt from this rule, eg schools.</p>\n\n<h2>Trade union membership</h2>\n\n<p>You must not use membership of a trade union as a factor in deciding whether to employ someone. This includes:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>not employing someone because they&rsquo;re a member of a trade union</li>\n  <li>insisting someone joins a trade union before you&rsquo;ll employ them</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Employing people with protected characteristics</h2>\n\n<p>You can choose a job candidate who has a protected characteristic over one who doesn&rsquo;t if they&rsquo;re as suitable for the job and you think that people with that characteristic:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>are underrepresented in the workforce, profession or industry </li>\n  <li>suffer a disadvantage connected to that characteristic (eg people from a certain ethnic group are not often given jobs in your sector)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You can only do this if you&rsquo;re trying to address the under-representation or disadvantage for that particular person. You must make decisions on a case by case basis and not because of a certain policy.</p>\n\n<p>You can&rsquo;t choose a candidate who isn&rsquo;t as suitable for the job just because they have a protected characteristic.</p>\n\n<h2>Disabled people</h2>\n\n<p>When recruiting you can treat a disabled person more favourably than a non-disabled person because of their disability.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/employer-preventing-discrimination/discrimination-during-employment","slug":"discrimination-during-employment","order":3,"title":"Discrimination during employment","body":"<p>You must not discriminate against your employees. This could be done by, for example:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>introducing measures that discriminate between workers, eg a benefit for married employees that&rsquo;s not available for people in a civil partnership</li>\n  <li>selecting someone for redundancy because they have a protected characteristic</li>\n  <li>failing to make reasonable adjustments for a disabled worker</li>\n  <li>firing someone for making an allegation of discrimination</li>\n  <li>firing someone because they&rsquo;re a union member</li>\n  <li>unfairly rejecting a <a href=\"/flexible-working\" title=\"Flexible working\">request for flexible working</a> from a new parent</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>This includes self-employed people on a contract for you.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Training and promotion can&rsquo;t just happen because of an employee&rsquo;s age or the time they&rsquo;ve worked for you.</p>\n\n<p>You are allowed to ask employees about their future career plans, including retirement. However, you shouldn&rsquo;t just choose older workers for discussions about retirement. Such talks should be part of general discussions about each worker&rsquo;s career development. </p>\n\n<h2>Employment tribunals</h2>\n\n<p>An employee who thinks they&rsquo;ve been discriminated against may raise a <a href=\"/solve-workplace-dispute/formal-procedures\" title=\"Formal procedures\">grievance</a> or take their case to an employment tribunal.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You are responsible for discrimination carried out by your employees unless you can show you’ve done everything you reasonably could to prevent or stop it.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Employing family members</h2>\n\n<p>If you hire members of your family you must:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>avoid special treatment in terms of pay, promotion and working conditions</li>\n  <li>make sure tax and <a href=\"/national-insurance\" title=\"National Insurance\">national insurance contributions</a> are done correctly</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Gender reassignment</h2>\n\n<p>The moment an employee tells their employer that they are going to have gender reassignment, they are protected from discrimination. This includes:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>disadvantaging the worker because of the time they may have to take off because of medical treatment</li>\n  <li>enabling the worker to use facilities appropriate to their gender</li>\n  <li>once the worker has a Gender Reassignment Certificate and a new birth certificate, you must amend your records, eg human resources records, to reflect this</li>\n  <li>insuring complete confidentiality of all information the worker gives you regarding their gender history </li>\n</ul>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/employer-preventing-discrimination/equal-pay","slug":"equal-pay","order":4,"title":"Equal pay","body":"<p>Women and men are entitled to be paid equal amounts for work of equal value - including benefits, eg company car.</p>\n\n<p>Employees can <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.equalityhumanrights.com/advice-and-guidance/tools-equal-pay/checklists-equal-pay-in-practice/16-obtaining-information-the-equal-pay-questions-form/\" title=\"Equal pay questions form\">make a request</a> for you to provide &lsquo;key information&rsquo; as part of a claim that they&rsquo;re not being paid what they should be. </p>\n\n<p>You don&rsquo;t have to respond to this request but it will be taken into account if there&rsquo;s an employment tribunal.</p>\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Recruiting and hiring","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Frecruiting-hiring.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes discrimination law, apprenticeships and using agencies","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Frecruiting-hiring","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/recruiting-hiring"},"parent":{"title":"Employing people","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes pay, contracts and hiring","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people"},"parent":null}},{"t