href=\"/flexible-working\" title=\"flexible working\">working flexibly</a>. </p>\n\n<p>Members of occupational pension schemes need to discuss with their pension scheme managers what impact a change in working hours or income might have on the pension, whether the scheme supports phased retirement and working beyond the scheme&rsquo;s normal pension age.</p>\n\n<p>Employers may or may not be able to agree requests. If an employee is unhappy with their employer&rsquo;s decision, they can challenge this at an <a href=\"/employment-tribunals\" title=\"employment tribunal\">employment tribunal</a>.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Retirement is a form of resignation - employers and employees must follow the right <a href=\"/handling-staff-resignations\" title=\"handling staff resignations\">procedures</a> for this.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>State Pension age</h2>\n\n<p>Retirement age is not the same as State Pension age which can be between 61 and 68, depending when someone was born and if they&rsquo;re male or female. Anyone can carry on working past State Pension age.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Calculate your <a href=\"/calculate-state-pension\" title=\"State Pension age calculator\">State Pension age</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n","alternative_title":""},"tags":[{"title":"Trade unions and workers rights","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Ftrade-unions.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes industrial action and recognising trade unions","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Ftrade-unions","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/trade-unions"},"parent":{"title":"Employing people","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes pay, contracts and hiring","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.g