//www.acas.org.uk/CHttpHandler.ashx?id=273&amp;p=0\" title=\"Download the 'Acas code of practice on disclosure of information to trade unions for collective bargaining' (PDF, 469KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download the ‘<abbr title=\"Advisory, Conciliation and Arbitration Service\">Acas</abbr> code of practice on disclosure of information to trade unions for collective bargaining’ (PDF, 469KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Collective agreements</h2>\n\n<p>If collective bargaining leads to an agreement, for example about a pay increase or change in working conditions, it&rsquo;s called a &lsquo;collective agreement&rsquo;.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/working-with-trade-unions/informing-and-consulting-with-unions","slug":"informing-and-consulting-with-unions","order":3,"title":"Informing and consulting with unions","body":"<p>Employers must inform and consult with a recognised trade union about:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>collective redundancies</li>\n  <li>transfers of business ownership</li>\n  <li>certain changes to pension schemes</li>\n  <li>health and safety</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If you fail to consult the union about any of these, you’ll be breaking the law and could be fined - the amount depends on the situation.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>There&rsquo;s more information on the pension scheme changes you have to consult about in the guidance below.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dwp.gov.uk/docs/occ-personal-pens-schemes-regs06.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Pension schemes - consultation guidance' (PDF, 168KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Pension schemes - consultation guidance’ (PDF, 168KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You can also make voluntary agreements with unions to regularly inform and consult them about other business and workplace issues.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Advisory, Conciliation and Arbitration Service\">Acas</abbr> has <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.acas.org.uk/index.aspx?articleid=663\" title