ed in administering the check off.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Even if you involve the union in the check-off, it’s still your responsibility to make sure you make check-off deductions properly.</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/working-with-trade-unions/rights-of-employees-in-trade-unions-","slug":"rights-of-employees-in-trade-unions-","order":5,"title":"Rights of employees in trade unions ","body":"<p>If you <a href=\"/recognise-a-trade-union\" title=\"recognise a union\">recognise a union</a>, it will normally name one or more of your workers as its local workplace representatives (&lsquo;reps&rsquo;).</p>\n\n<p>Union reps have certain <a href=\"/rights-of-trade-union-reps\" title=\"rights of trade union reps\">rights</a>. They&rsquo;re allowed reasonable time off work:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>with pay</strong> for union duties and training at appropriate times</li>\n  <li><strong>without pay</strong> to take part in union activities, eg the union’s annual conference (trade union members are entitled to this as well)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Reasonable time off doesn’t have to taken as annual leave.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Blacklisting</h2>\n\n<p>You can&rsquo;t discriminate against anyone because they&rsquo;re in the union or because of their union activity.</p>\n\n<p>With rare exceptions, it&rsquo;s also illegal to compile, use, sell or supply a &lsquo;blacklist&rsquo; of union members that will be used to discriminate against them.</p>\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Trade unions and workers rights","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Ftrade-unions.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes industrial action and recognising trade unions","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Ftrade-unions","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/trade-unions"},"parent":{"ti